Nope. Always lots to do actually. Real problem is, people don't want to do things that don't drop loot. And you really can't implement virtual spaces with decent loot unless you have some way to move items out of the economy. Otherwise, you reach the saturation point and the loot it has is then essentially the same as no loot and you end up with the exact same problem. Virtual spaces in this game would solve nothing for that reason, something all the proponents ignore on a regular basis. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4380">Qaman</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
